Natasha Hope-Simpson lost a part of her leg in a hit-and-run accident in 2013 . 
  She has a prosthetic leg below the knee and uses a cane to walk . 
  She received angry notes on her windshield scolding her for parking in a handicap space . 
  She said she was flattered that someone could not tell she was missing her leg because her prosthetic was covered . 
 